The paper discusses a system for analyzing large graphs, which involves manipulating raw input data tables and applying graph analytics functions. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to data management, data mining, and graph algorithms. Specifically, cs.DB (databases), cs.SI (social and information networks), and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) are all relevant sub-categories for graph analysis. Additionally, cs.CE (computational engineering, finance, and science) and cs.IR (information retrieval) could also be relevant given the potential applications of graph analysis in these fields.
